<br>
Also, a casting mob offers an extra safety margin.   Melee mob is guaranteed to rush you the moment charm breaks.   A caster might stop and begin casting - which often will give you time to recharm.   Even if he finishes casting before you do, with good enough resists you can simply shrug it off. <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Bregalad Alcarin</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, High Elf Phantasmist, Xev &lt;Legends of Westwood&gt;<br>
